                            <comment id="14472266" author="melix" created="Fri, 27 Jan 2012 10:26:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;confirmed on 1.8.5 and master too&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472346" author="melix" created="Fri, 27 Jan 2012 10:35:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is most likely due to the fact you&apos;ve written &lt;tt&gt;writer.setRAMBufferSizeMB(defaultRamBufferSize())&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;writer.setRAMBufferSizeMB(defaultRamBufferSize)&lt;/tt&gt; (defaultRamBufferSize is an int, not a method nor a closure). However, a VerifyError should not happen.=&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472387" author="melix" created="Fri, 27 Jan 2012 10:51:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached a simpler example which triggers the same error (on 1.8.X, not on master, where an NPE is thrown instead).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472221" author="melix" created="Fri, 27 Jan 2012 10:53:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stripped down:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Bar {
   &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; defaultValue = 40
   void m() {
    defaultValue()
   }
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Bar().m()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472294" author="jprobichaud" created="Fri, 27 Jan 2012 11:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;oh, wow, good catch &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; removing this typo (not sure why I ended up with that, I&apos;m currently re-factoring some code) makes everything working properly now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess a &quot;no such method&quot; exception would have been better &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472402" author="blackdrag" created="Sat, 28 Jan 2012 04:05:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I set it as critical bug for 1.8,so we don&apos;t forget about this one&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
